  "prompt": "What is stannic hydroxide?",
  "response": "Stannic hydroxide is a chemical compound with the formula Sn(OH)\u2084. It consists of tin (Sn) in its +4 oxidation state and hydroxide (OH) groups. Stannic hydroxide is an amphoteric compound, meaning it can react both as an acid and as a base. It can be formed by the reaction of tin(IV) salts with alkali. It's not typically found in a pure form and is usually encountered in hydrated forms or as part of other compounds. In aqueous solutions, it can exist as tin oxide hydrate.",
